sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Client as Client (WS / SDK)
    participant DO as Rust DurableObject (workers-rs)
    participant WASM as rquickjs engine.wasm
    participant Delta as W5+W4+E6 delta stack
    participant SQL as DO SQLite (chunks + manifest)
    participant R2 as R2 engram-snapshots

    Note over Client,R2: LIVE SESSION — eval + per-cell snapshot

    Client->>DO: eval(cell)
    activate DO
    DO->>WASM: run cell on live linear memory
    activate WASM
    WASM-->>DO: result (effects fire ONCE)
    deactivate WASM
    Note right of WASM: heap mutated in place — (WASM linear memory is monotonic)

    DO->>Delta: used-heap admission + arena scrub
    activate Delta
    Note right of Delta: admit on QuickJS used heap (not raw buffer), scrub freed pages
    DO->>WASM: dump memory.buffer (+ globals + tables)
    WASM-->>DO: raw heap image
    Delta->>Delta: 256B byte-delta vs prior image
    Delta->>Delta: E6 oplog crash-tail + engine-hash
    Delta-->>DO: changed chunks only
    deactivate Delta

    alt image gz <= 2 MB
        DO->>SQL: write changed ~64KB chunks + manifest (used_heap, kv_json)
        SQL-->>DO: committed (crash-atomic)
    else image gz > 2 MB
        DO->>R2: put full image
        DO->>SQL: write manifest pointer (r2)
    end
    DO-->>Client: {ok, value preview}
    deactivate DO

    Note over Client,R2: IDLE — DO evicted, in-memory kernel GONE

    rect rgb(31,111,235)
    Note over DO,WASM: generation N -> N+1 — no source replay
    end

    Client->>DO: ping / eval (cold wake)
    activate DO
    DO->>SQL: read manifest (used_heap, engine-hash, kv_json)
    SQL-->>DO: manifest
    Note right of DO: RESTORE guard admits on — recorded used_heap, not raw bytes

    alt manifest -> sqlite
        DO->>SQL: read chunks
        SQL-->>DO: chunk rows
    else manifest -> r2
        DO->>R2: get image
        R2-->>DO: image bytes
    end

    DO->>Delta: reconstruct full image (apply deltas + E6 tail)
    Delta-->>DO: coherent raw heap image
    DO->>WASM: new instance + Tier-0 natives at fixed bases
    activate WASM
    DO->>WASM: blit memory.buffer (+ globals + tables)
    Note right of WASM: live state restored, — NO replay, NO re-fired effects
    WASM-->>DO: ready (sqlite-restore / r2-restore)
    deactivate WASM
    DO-->>Client: resumed (gen N+1, state intact)
    deactivate DO
